block content
  .container
    header.partners--title
      h3  Partners
  .partners--intro
    .container
      h3 We have a massive opportunity <br> to build a sustainable society
      p The Sustainable Development Goals were adopted by the UN in September 2015, setting the agenda for development in all countries up to 2030. The 17 goals are the result of a 2 year, consultative process and shows what the world thinks a good, fulfilling life should be made of. Topics like access to water, clean energy, a healthy environment and education are all included side-by-side, noting the links and potential conflicts between a number of the goals - like the impact of increasing energy access on the environment, or the potential impacts of increased food production on water.
  .container.partners--cards
    .partners--card
      a(href='partners-wri.html')
        img(src='img/logo-1-th.png')
      p The World Resources Institute (WRI) is a global research organization that spans more than 50 countries. We convene over 450 experts to work closely with leaders to turn big ideas into actions that sustain our natural resources—the foundation of economic opportunity and human well-being.
      a(href='partners-wri.html') Read more

    .partners--card
      a(href='partners-vizzuality.html')
        img(src='img/logo-2-th.png')
      p Vizzuality is a world-renowned digital agency, delivering bespoke, beautiful visualisations and tools to the most important organisations in the world. Pushing the boundaries of how data is stored, shared and visualised, we help to improve our world one visualisation at a time.
      a(href='partners-vizzuality.html') Read more

    .partners--card
      a.is-disabled(href='#')
        img(src='img/logo-3-th.png')
      p Google Earth Engine brings together the world's satellite imagery and makes it available online alongside tools for scientists, independent researchers and nations to mine this massive warehouse of data.
      a.is-disabled(href='#') Read more

    .partners--card
      a.is-disabled(href='#')
        img(src='img/logo-4-th.png')
      p The easiest way to make maps online. Since launching in 2012 over 130,000 people have used it to create data-driven maps, which enable visual discovery of trends and patterns, and make better, faster decisions.
      a.is-disabled(href='#') Read more

    .partners--card
      a.is-disabled(href='#')
        img(src='img/logo-5-th.png')
      p DigitalGlobe is a leading provider of high‑resolution Earth imagery products and services. Sourced from our own advanced satellite constellation, our imagery solutions support a wide variety of uses, including environmental monitoring.
      a.is-disabled(href='#') Read more

    .partners--card
      a.is-disabled(href='#')
        img(src='img/logo-6-th.png')
      p The Earth Genome is enabling the world's key institutions to fully account for natural capital in all their decisions. We are connecting the world's best earth data, scientists, and technology providers to drive insight and innovation for governments, NGOs, corporations, and investors.
      a.is-disabled(href='#') Read more
    .partners--card
      a.is-disabled(href='#')
        img(src='img/logo-8-th.png')
      p Our mission is to better understand planet Earth by analyzing massive amounts of imagery. We’ll begin this journey by understanding satellite imagery to enable real-time global awareness — whether it’s food production, energy infrastructure, the growth of cities, or our impact on the environment. Not only will we identify what’s in a single image, but we’ll also be looking at how our Earth changes over time.
      a.is-disabled(href='#') Read more

